  <prompt>Add a smoke test asserting that TL;DR's `totalNotificationCount` equals the number of items rendered in Activity Notes. Reconcile via single source of truth (input payload to playbook = items displayed by widget). Mock input with N items in 3 categories; assert widget header count equals visible card count.</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. Expert in Fluent UI v9 + React hooks + Xrm.WebApi.</role>
  <goal>Smoke test passes: given N mocked notifications across 3 categories, the TL;DR header shows totalNotificationCount=N and the ActivityNotesSection renders exactly N visible items.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>FR-20: UAT defect — TL;DR count diverged from visible items. The fix is single-source-of-truth wiring: the input payload to playbook equals the items the widget displays. This test guards that invariant.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/DailyBriefingApp.tsx</file>
